@startuml subsistemaSnapshots
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #07090F
skinparam defaultFontColor #E2E8F5
skinparam ArrowColor #38BDF8
skinparam classBackgroundColor #141824
skinparam classBorderColor #2A3850
skinparam classFontColor #E2E8F5
skinparam packageBackgroundColor #0D1018
skinparam packageBorderColor #2A3850
skinparam packageFontColor #38BDF8
skinparam databaseBackgroundColor #1E293B
skinparam databaseBorderColor #38BDF8
skinparam databaseFontColor #E2E8F5
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #141824
skinparam noteBorderColor #38BDF8

title Subsistema de Snapshots · SnapshotService ↔ SnapshotRepository ↔ MongoDB

package "VISOR DE SNAPSHOTS · React 18 + Vite (puerto 3001)" as FE2 {
  class "Páginas con datos en persistencia\nHome · MetricSnapshots\nChartSnapshots · EntitySnapshots\nSnapshotDetail" as Pages2
  class "Renderizadores por subtipo\n(gauge, charts, fichas)\nreconstruyen la vista\na partir del JSON guardado" as Renderers
  class "API Client (axios)\nBearer JWT" as API2
  Pages2 --> Renderers
  Pages2 --> API2
}
API2 --> "app/routes/" : HTTP · :3001 → /api\n(Vite proxy en dev)
package "app/routes/" {
  class "snapshots.py\n(snapshots.router)" as RT #0F1E2A {
    +POST /snapshots/metrics
    +POST /snapshots/charts
    +POST /snapshots/entities
    +GET  /snapshots/{type}
    +GET  /snapshots/{type}/{id}
    +DELETE /snapshots/{type}/{id}
  }
}

package "app/services/" {
  class SnapshotService #0F1E2A {
    +save_metric(payload, cu)
    +save_chart(payload, cu)
    +save_entity(payload, cu)
    +list(type, filters, page)
    +get_by_id(type, id)
    +delete(type, id)
    --
    -_normalize_params(params)
    -_compute_params_hash(params)
    -_build_actor(cu)
    -_today_utc()
  }
}

package "app/schemas/" {
  class "snapshot.py" as SCH #0F1E2A {
    MetricSnapshot
    ChartSnapshot
    EntitySnapshot
    SnapshotActor
  }
}

package "app/repositories/" {
  class "snapshot.py\n(SnapshotRepository)" as REPO #0F1E2A {
    +insert_one(type, doc)
    +find_one(type, key)
    +update_one(type, id, patch)
    +find_many(type, filters,\n  page, page_size)
    +find_by_id(type, id)
    +delete_one(type, id)
  }
}

package "app/core/" {
  class "mongo.py" as MG #0F1E2A {
    +get_client()
    +get_db()
    +ensure_indexes()
  }
}

database "MongoDB" as DB #0F1E2A {
  class "metric_snapshots" as C1 {
    unique: (metric_name,
    params_hash,
    snapshot_date)
  }
  class "chart_snapshots" as C2 {
    unique: (chart_name,
    params_hash,
    snapshot_date)
  }
  class "entity_snapshots" as C3 {
    unique: (entity_type,
    entity_id,
    snapshot_date)
  }
}

RT --> SnapshotService
SnapshotService ..> SCH : serializa /\ndeserializa
SnapshotService --> REPO
REPO --> MG
MG --> DB
C1 -[hidden]down- C2
C2 -[hidden]down- C3

note right of SnapshotService
  **Lógica principal:**
  1. Normalizar los parámetros.
  2. Crear un hash de los parámetros normalizados.
  3. Registrar la fecha y el usuario que lo solicita.
  4. Si ya existe una captura hoy con esos parámetros, 
     se actualiza. Si no existe, se crea una nueva.
end note

note bottom of REPO
  **Único repositorio sin SQLAlchemy.**
  API homogénea sobre las 3 colecciones.
  No tiene dependencias cruzadas con
  ningún otro repositorio del sistema.
end note

note bottom of DB
  **RNF-16 · Clave compuesta única.**
  El índice único garantiza a nivel de BD
  la restricción de una snapshot por tipo,
  parámetros y día.
end note

@enduml
